Iraqi President Saddam Hussein carriedout his first major government shakeup in five years tonight,naming a new oil minister in shuffling three posts.    One minister was dropped in the shuffle, announced in apresidential decree. It gave no reason for the changes in thegovernment of the Arab Baath Socialist Party which has ruledIraq since a revolution in 1968.    The decree named the head of the Iraqi National Oil Company(INOC), Isam Abdul-Rahim al-Chalaby, to take over as oilminister replacing Qassem Ahmed Taqi.    Taqi, appointed oil minister in the last significantgovernment reorganization in 1982, was moved to be minister ofheavy industries. Reuter&#3;